sections.title: How the population has changed in Merton
sections.label: Select another local authority

sections.content: In 2020, Merton was the 28th largest local authority in London, with a total population of 206,453. A decrease compared with 2019.

sections.title: Population density in Merton
sections.content: In 2020, the population density in Merton was 5,487 people per square kilometre, which was less than London (5,727), and more than the United Kingdom as a whole (276).

sections.title: Median age in Merton
sections.content: In 2020, the median age in Merton was 38 years, which was older than London (36 years), and younger than the United Kingdom as a whole (41 years).
